title: Glenn Youngkin Wins Virginia Governor Race
sub_head: Race ends years of Democratic gains in the state and gives GOP a playbook ahead of midterms
body:
Republican Glenn Youngkin was elected governor of Virginia on Tuesday, halting a yearslong trend of Democratic electoral gains in the state and giving the GOP a potential playbook in competitive parts of the U.S. ahead of next yearâ€™s congressional midterm elections.
Mr. Youngkin, a 54-year-old former private-equity executive and political newcomer, defeated Democrat Terry McAuliffe, a party stalwart who served as governor from 2014 to 2018, according to the Associated Press.
